<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mouly &amp; De Block" authorityYear="2008" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coptosperma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Coptosperma mitochondrioides" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mitochondrioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Coptosperma mitochondrioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mouly &amp; De Block by the triangular, keeled stipules with a robust awn (vs. stipules of the &quot;bec du canard&quot; type with rounded tip) and the smooth fruits (vs. fruits with ca. 10 longitudinal ribs).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
